s0121: Nineteenth year, Jin Quwo first became Jin Hou.
s0122: Duke Huan of Qi became hegemon at Juan.
s0123: Twentieth year, Duke Wu died, buried at Yong Pingyang.
s0124: First time using humans to follow in death; those who followed in death were sixty-six people.
s0125: He had one son, named Bai; Bai was not established, enfeoffed at Pingyang.
s0126: Established his younger brother Duke De.
s0127: Duke De of Qin first year, first resided in Yong city's Grand Zheng Palace.
s0128: Used 300 sacrificial animals to worship at the Fu altar.
s0130: Later descendants watered horses at the Yellow River.
s0131: Duke Liang of Liang and Duke Rui of Rui came to court.
s0132: Second year, Duke De died, his son Duke Xuan ascended.
s0133: Duke Xuan of Qin first year, the Qin people moved to Yong.
s0134: Second year, established the Zhi altar.
s0135: Third year, established the Yong altar.
s0136: Fourth year, Duke Xuan died, his son Duke Cheng ascended.
s0137: Duke Cheng of Qin first year, attacked the Quanrong.
s0138: Second year, established the Xingle altar.
s0148: Twelfth year, Duke Cheng died, his son Duke Mu ascended.
s0149: Duke Mu of Qin first year, began to use coins.
s0150: Second year, established the Xingle altar.
s0152: Fourth year, established the Wu altar.
s0180: Thirty-second year, Duke Mu died, his son Duke Kang ascended.
